Class JsonHttpClient

JSON HTTP Client.

Implementation is not thread-safe.

Class JsonHttpClient.Builder, GenericUrl getBaseUrl()

Returns the base URL of the service, for example {@code "https://www.googleapis.com/tasks/v1/"}. Must be URL-encoded and must end with a "/". This is determined when the library is generated and normally should not be changed.

Use this method only if {@code baseUrl} is used instead of {@code rootUrl} and {@code servicePath}.

@deprecated (scheduled to be removed in 1.1112) Use .getRootUrl and .getServicePath instead.

Class JsonHttpClient.Builder, Builder setBaseUrl(GenericUrl)

Sets the base URL of the service, for example {@code "https://www.googleapis.com/tasks/v1/"}. Must be URL-encoded and must end with a "/". This is determined when the library is generated and normally should not be changed. Subclasses should override by calling super.

Use this method only if {@code baseUrl} is used instead of {@code rootUrl} and {@code servicePath}.

@since 1.7 @deprecated (scheduled to be removed in 1.1112) Use .setRootUrl and .setServicePath instead.
Class JsonHttpClient.Builder, Builder setRootUrl(String)

Sets the root URL of the service, for example {@code https://www.googleapis.com/}. Must be URL-encoded and must end with a "/". This is determined when the library is generated and and normally should be changed. Subclasses should override by calling super.

If the specified root URL does not end with a "/" then a "/" is added to the end.

Use this method only if {@code rootUrl} and {@code servicePath} are used instead of {@code baseUrl}.

@since 1.10

Class JsonHttpParser

Parses HTTP JSON response content into an data class of key/value pairs.

Implementation is thread-safe.

Sample usage: 

 
  static void setParser(HttpRequest request) {
    request.addParser(new JsonHttpParser(new JacksonFactory()));
  }
@since 1.0 @author Yaniv Inbar @deprecated (scheduled to be removed in 1.1112) Use JsonObjectParser instead.
